cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.CYBER 

This paper is likely to belong to the Social and Information Retrieval sub-categories of Computer Science. The paper analyzes Facebook accounts used by Like Farms and compares their activities to a baseline sample of normal users. This involves crawling their timelines, retrieving the pages they like, and clustering their activity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Retrieval) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). 

The paper also deals with reputation manipulation activities and anti-fraud tools, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper involves analyzing text data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
